statements: CREATE TABLE FitnessData (id INT PRIMARY KEY, user_id INT INT, workout_type VARCHAR(50), workout_duration INT, calories_burned INT);
CREATE TABLE FitnessUser ( user_id INT PRIMARY KEY, username VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL, age INT, gender VARCHAR(10) NOT NULL, height FLOAT, weight FLOAT )

CREATE TABLE FitnessActivity ( activity_id INT PRIMARY KEY, user_id INT, activity_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL, activity_date DATE, duration_minutes INT, calories_burned FLOAT, FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES FitnessUser(user_id) )
CREATE TABLE ExampleTable ( example_id INT PRIMARY KEY, example_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL, example_description TEXT )
CREATE TABLE workout_plan (plan_id INT PRIMARY KEY, plan_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL, plan_description TEXT, plan_duration INT);
CREATE TABLE exercise (exercise_id INT PRIMARY KEY, exercise_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL, muscle_group VARCHAR(100), difficulty_level ENUM('Beginner', 'Intermediate', 'Advanced'));
CREATE TABLE user_statistics (user_id INT PRIMARY KEY, username VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL, age INT, height FLOAT, weight FLOAT, workout_days INT);
CREATE TABLE example_users (id UUID PRIMARY KEY, username VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL, email VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL, age INT);
CREATE TABLE example_workouts (id UUID PRIMARY KEY, user_id UUID REFERENCES example_users(id), workout_type VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL, duration INTERVAL);
CREATE TABLE example_exercises (id UUID PRIMARY KEY, exercise_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL, muscle_group VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL);
